## Image Generation Prompts

### Prompt 1: In-Game Chibi Sprite (Reference Sheet)
*(Feed the approved Cleopastar illustration as reference image. Describe only pose and motion.)*

Chibi pixel art sprite sheet, front-facing full body, isolated on black background. Six frames arranged in a single row: Idle, Walk, Jump, BA (Basic Attack), Shift, E Skill. Same character design as the reference. All animations restrained and elegant вҖ” no exaggerated limb swings, no wide stances.
- **Idle:** Standing upright, one hand resting lightly on the ankh cane. Subtle slow breathing motion only. Expression neutral and cold.
- **Walk:** Small measured steps, upright posture maintained at all times. Cane carried at her side, not swinging. Head does not bob. She glides more than she walks.
- **Jump:** Legs draw up slightly and neatly beneath her. Free hand remains close to the body. No flailing. Composed mid-air posture, as if she is being lifted rather than jumping.
- **BA (Basic Attack):** A single, precise outward gesture of the free hand вҖ” as if flicking something away dismissively. No wind-up, no follow-through. Economy of motion.
- **Shift (Nut's Decree):** She raises the ankh cane forward in a deliberate, slow-extended point. One fluid motion. Posture unchanged. Like issuing a quiet royal command.
- **E Skill (Apep's Maw):** She glances downward with mild disdain, raises her free hand slightly palm outward. A restrained, minimal gesture. No dramatic pose.

Consistent pixel art style across all frames, bold outlines, clean limited color palette.

### Prompt 2: Character Poster
*(Feed the approved Cleopastar illustration as reference image. Describe only pose, expression, and composition.)*

Character poster, same design as the reference image. Cleopastar stands in a three-quarter front pose, weight shifted slightly onto one leg, ankh cane held loosely at her side вҖ” neither gripping it tightly nor brandishing it. Her chin is tilted just slightly upward. Eyes half-lidded, gaze directed downward and to the side as if the viewer is barely worth acknowledging. No smile, no frown вҖ” the expression of someone who has already decided they are the most important person in the room. Her posture is completely still, composed, regal. Multiple glowing five-pointed stars float at different heights around her вҖ” some golden-teal (Immature), one deep violet with a radial distortion haze (Blackhole). Dark starry background with subtle golden light. Dramatic lighting from slightly below, casting a soft upward glow on her face. The overall feeling: a queen who does not need to prove anything.

---

## Decisions log

- **Five active stars and a 60 m flight ceiling.** Cleopastar can prepare a meaningful
  formation without filling the arena with unbounded projectiles or firing across the
  entire map.
- **Shift converges on a captured point.** Each star now has its own path to the same
  aim point, passes through it, and is stopped only by terrain/collision/lifetime. This
  makes setup geometry and prediction central to her sniper identity.
- **Repeated-hit reduction is a Shift-volley rule, not a target debuff.** Normal
  stationary-star explosions retain their full damage and there is no lingering
  StarSicking state on foes.
- **Star SoftVolume consumes only on an exhausted jump.** It is an enterable, momentary
  movement tool rather than a physical landing surface; its ordinary Normal explosion
  never hurts Cleo.
- **Shift volleys do not share reduction.** Every Shift creates a fresh per-target
  sequence, keeping its reward readable and preventing old projectiles from carrying
  invisible damage history into a later cast.
- **Ammo persists while benched.** Ammo count and reload progress follow the normal
  background cooldown schedule, preventing Tab from becoming a free reload.
- **Ultimate deferred.** It will return only after the game-wide Ultimate model exists.

